article.headline: SE Louisiana 75, Cent. Arkansas 64
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Southeastern Louisiana's Patrick Sullivan scored 22 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead the Lions to a 75-64 Southland Conference win Wednesday night over Central Arkansas. The victory broke a six-game losing streak on the road for SE Louisiana (9-10, 3-3 SLC). The Lions led 32-27 at the half. UCA (9-10, 2-4) shot poorly from the field for the game, hitting only 33 percent of its attempts while SE Louisiana was sinking shots at a 48 percent rate. Warrell Span added 13 points for the Lions, while Damon Forest came off the bench to score 10. Sullivan wasn't the only player with double-digit figures for both points and rebounds. UCA's Chris Brown scored 18 points and got 13 boards. Marcus Pillow scored 17 points for the Bears, and Mitch Rueter had 15.
